  "texts": [
    "In particular, P vanishes if and only if the flow of X V preserves H. Notice that the condition that ρ(π 1 (B)) ≤ Aut ±1 (N) is equivalent to the existence of a globally-defined volume element for the fibres of adM which is ∇ ad -parallel.",
    "This allows us to define the relative volume density √ det h: B → R + of the bundle metric h on adM.",
    "Since we are locally in a principal bundle, the mean curvature vector H satisfies π * H =: H = -∇ log √ det h. Combining with the theory developed in [BL23a] (in the case of principal bundles), this also allows us to consider the β + ad -weighted volume density of the fibres v ad β +: B → R, see [BL23b,§3] for further details about this function.",
    "We note that, even though those references are in the context of untwisted principal bundles, the Aut(𝔫)-invariance of the β-volume density v β and the fact that the structure group of M is contained in the affine group of N, imply that v ad β + is well defined.In the following theorem, we make use of the 'weighted Laplacian' ∆ m = div m •∇.",
    "Here div m is the divergence operator with respect to the weighted measuredm:= e -f √ det h dvol ǧ,where dvol ǧ is the Riemannian volume density of (B, ǧ)."
